## OpenTelemetry

Register tracing, metrics, and logging exporters at startup:

```csharp
builder.Services.AddOpenTelemetry()
    .WithTracing(tracing => tracing
        .AddAspNetCoreInstrumentation()
        .AddHttpClientInstrumentation()
        .AddEntityFrameworkCoreInstrumentation()
        .AddOtlpExporter())
    .WithMetrics(metrics => metrics
        .AddAspNetCoreInstrumentation()
        .AddRuntimeInstrumentation()
        .AddOtlpExporter());
```

- Use `ActivitySource` for custom spans in application and domain layer operations
- Do not add custom spans for framework operations already instrumented (HTTP, EF Core)
- Export to OTLP; avoid vendor-specific SDKs in application code

```csharp
private static readonly ActivitySource Source = new("MyApp.Orders");

public async Task<Result<Guid>> Handle(PlaceOrderCommand command, CancellationToken ct)
{
    using var activity = Source.StartActivity("PlaceOrder");
    activity?.SetTag("order.customerId", command.CustomerId);
    // ...
}
```

