## Minimal API vs controller observability

In Minimal APIs, use endpoint filters for cross-cutting logging rather than middleware when the concern is endpoint-specific:

```csharp
app.MapPost("/orders", HandleAsync)
   .AddEndpointFilter<RequestLoggingFilter>();
```

In controller-based APIs, use action filters or global filters registered in `AddControllers()`.

Do not mix both approaches within the same application.

---

## Antipatterns

| Pattern | Issue |
|---------|-------|
| String interpolation in `ILogger` | Loses structured fields; prevents log indexing |
| Logging inside domain entities | Domain layer must not reference infrastructure |
| `Console.WriteLine` for diagnostics | Not captured by log pipeline; lost in production |
| Swallowing exceptions before logging | Loses root cause; debug becomes impossible |
| Correlation ID generated per log line | Must be generated once per request and propagated |
| Vendor SDK in application layer | Couples domain/application code to observability vendor |
